==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calypso
<hw>Ca*lyp"so</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧*l⟦icr⟧p"s⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[The Latinized Greek name of a beautiful nymph.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small and beautiful species of orchid, having a
flower variegated with purple, pink, and yellow. It grows in cold and
wet localities in the northern part of the United States. The
<spn>Calypso borealis</spn> is the only orchid which reaches 68⟦deg⟧
N.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>calypter</ent>⟦br⟧
